      • octTreeInsert

        boolean octTreeInsert(T item)
               throws IllegalArgumentException
        Insert the object item into the octtree.

        The function returns false if the object could not be inserted for any reason (perhaps due to being too large).

        Parameters:
        item - The object to insert
        Returns:
        true if the object was inserted
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the object's bounding volume is not well-formed.
        See Also:
        BoundingVolumeCheck.isWellFormed(BoundingVolumeType)

      • octTreeIterateObjects

        <E extends Throwable> void octTreeIterateObjects(com.io7m.jfunctional.PartialFunctionType<T,Boolean,E> f)
                                          throws E extends Throwable
        Pass each object in the octtree to f.call(), in no particular order. Iteration stops if f.call() returns false, or raises an exception.
        Type Parameters:
        E - The type of raised exceptions.
        Parameters:
        f - The function that will receive each object
        Throws:
        E - Propagated from f.call()
        E extends Throwable

      • octTreeQueryRaycast

        void octTreeQueryRaycast(RayI3D ray,
                         SortedSet<OctTreeRaycastResult<T>> items)
                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Returns the objects intersected by the ray ray in items. The objects are returned in order of increasing scalar distance from the origin of ray. That is, the nearest object to the origin of ray will be the first item in items.
        Parameters:
        ray - The ray
        items - The returned objects
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the object's bounding volume is not well-formed.
        See Also:
        VectorI3D.distance(com.io7m.jtensors.VectorReadable3DType, com.io7m.jtensors.VectorReadable3DType), BoundingVolumeCheck.isWellFormed(BoundingVolumeType)

      • octTreeQueryVolumeContaining

                                  SortedSet<T> items)
                           throws IllegalArgumentException

        Parameters:

        items - The returned items
        Throws:

      • octTreeRemove

        boolean octTreeRemove(T item)
               throws IllegalArgumentException
        Remove the object item from the octtree.

        The function returns false if the object could not be removed for any reason (perhaps due to not being in the tree in the first place).

        Parameters:
        item - The object to remove
        Returns:
        true if the object was removed
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the object's bounding volume is not well-formed.
        See Also:
        BoundingVolumeCheck.isWellFormed(BoundingVolumeType)
